Wash and dry produce.

Thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

== Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, scallion
greens, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, and half the
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}.

== Chicken ==

Break up @sous vide chopped chicken{8%oz} in package and drain any excess
liquid. Heat a @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add scallion whites, chicken, and @garlic powder{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned and warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add
@sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, remaining chili sauce, and @water{1/4%cup};
cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute} more.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve and toast @demi-baguettes{2%unit}.

Fill baguettes with chicken, slaw, and @crispy fried onions{1%unit}. Divide
sandwiches between plates and serve.

> This sando has it all: sweet, salty, tangy, spicy, and of course, crunchy!